[SPEAKER_02]: I would just add to that point.

465
00:48:42,423 --> 00:48:45,985
[SPEAKER_02]: Definitely agree with President Morrell, Councillor Scarpelli.

466
00:48:46,005 --> 00:48:51,350
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, when we receive a budget, I'm hoping to be able to

467
00:48:52,747 --> 00:49:00,371
[SPEAKER_02]: take a look at the bottom lines and try to present the information in a more, maybe, you know, I hope it's presented in maybe a more comprehensive way in the budget.

468
00:49:00,391 --> 00:49:01,032
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't know yet.

469
00:49:02,473 --> 00:49:11,117
[SPEAKER_02]: Certainly last year when we were putting together sheets and sheets of paper and didn't have anything that was that, you know, we talk about a circus, that was the circus.

470
00:49:11,158 --> 00:49:13,679
[SPEAKER_02]: We never got a complete budget in the first place.

471
00:49:13,739 --> 00:49:19,923
[SPEAKER_02]: And that's why we were asking questions that in a normal year we would have had the information in advance and wouldn't have had to ask.

472
00:49:20,923 --> 00:49:25,614
[SPEAKER_02]: likely, I think would have had more time to not have things go to the last minute on the last day.

473
00:49:25,634 --> 00:49:30,344
[SPEAKER_02]: Now, who knows, you know, that's Monday morning quarterbacking, but, um,

474
00:49:31,660 --> 00:49:34,462
[SPEAKER_02]: I would really say yes, definitely at this point, it's in the hands of the mayor.

475
00:49:35,804 --> 00:49:41,929
[SPEAKER_02]: When it's released publicly, that's when, you know, it'll be released publicly, that's when we get it, the mayor's proposal.

476
00:49:43,070 --> 00:49:54,980
[SPEAKER_02]: And I'm gonna take a look at it and I'm hoping the information will be there that I'll be able to say, okay, now I understand why we had a free cash surplus last year and here's what's being proposed and here's how much one-time funding is being used.

477
00:49:55,060 --> 00:49:55,941
[SPEAKER_02]: And then,

478
00:49:57,562 --> 00:50:09,994
[SPEAKER_02]: If that is not made clear from the presentation in that proposal, I'll try to bring something to a future council meeting myself, you know, basically just share with the public what I the work that I tried to understand the document.

479
00:50:10,554 --> 00:50:13,597
[SPEAKER_02]: So, at that point I think we'll have a much clearer understanding of.

480
00:50:14,478 --> 00:50:23,024
[SPEAKER_02]: How much one time funding are we using some shape of what the fiscal cliff we're looking at is in the next budget if it's not already in this budget.

481
00:50:23,965 --> 00:50:29,629
[SPEAKER_02]: Things that aren't funded, and potentially even again like we had last year what's the amount of money.

482
00:50:30,470 --> 00:50:33,511
[SPEAKER_02]: That's not here that we need now to fund essential services.

483
00:50:33,591 --> 00:50:36,111
[SPEAKER_02]: And is there a real revenue proposal to get that money?

484
00:50:36,291 --> 00:50:38,932
[SPEAKER_02]: So that's something that I'm hoping to do.

485
00:50:39,092 --> 00:50:47,193
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't have enough data to do that yet, which is one reason it's very difficult to answer your question at this time about what can we do?

486
00:50:47,613 --> 00:50:49,553
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't know how bad it is yet or how good it is.

487
00:50:51,014 --> 00:50:51,314
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

488
00:50:51,674 --> 00:50:52,934
[SPEAKER_07]: And I will go ahead.

489
00:50:53,234 --> 00:50:56,075
[SPEAKER_04]: I'll present one last question and I won't be late with this one.

490
00:50:59,665 --> 00:51:01,185
[SPEAKER_04]: Who's going to present the budget this year?

491
00:51:01,786 --> 00:51:02,886
[SPEAKER_04]: Who's going to answer the budget questions?

492
00:51:03,826 --> 00:51:04,806
[SPEAKER_04]: We don't have a budget director.

493
00:51:06,046 --> 00:51:07,206
[SPEAKER_07]: I do not know.

494
00:51:07,266 --> 00:51:08,307
[SPEAKER_07]: I can ask the administration.

495
00:51:08,927 --> 00:51:13,007
[SPEAKER_07]: I was going to say, do you have anything else you want to add?

496
00:51:13,348 --> 00:51:15,808
[SPEAKER_07]: I did speak with the chief of staff, I believe it was Thursday.

497
00:51:16,548 --> 00:51:18,829
[SPEAKER_07]: They're still hopeful that they will get us the budget this Friday.

498
00:51:19,509 --> 00:51:25,450
[SPEAKER_07]: If we do get the budget this Friday, I will gleefully schedule budget meetings starting next Tuesday.

499
00:51:27,288 --> 00:51:44,628
[SPEAKER_07]: So, but I will absolutely make sure we I will ask who is going to be presenting, and I will make sure you know a we're not meeting until we get a budget book, and be that we have the time to actually sit with it and digest it and you know come prepared and make the best use of everyone's time, the public bars department heads everyone.

500
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,381
[SPEAKER_07]: Any further discussion, vice-president Behrs?

501
00:51:48,521 --> 00:51:57,845
[SPEAKER_02]: I would just move to submit any written documents on recommendations provided by councillors as well as the committee report to the mayor for consideration.

502
00:51:57,865 --> 00:51:59,966
[SPEAKER_07]: Do you have it, Mr. Clerk?

503
00:52:00,246 --> 00:52:03,568
[SPEAKER_07]: Would you like to add adjourning to that?

504
00:52:03,588 --> 00:52:04,068
[SPEAKER_02]: And adjourn.

505
00:52:04,128 --> 00:52:04,368
[SPEAKER_07]: Great.

506
00:52:04,928 --> 00:52:06,129
[SPEAKER_02]: Adjourn is good.

507
00:52:06,729 --> 00:52:12,572
[SPEAKER_06]: Are we expecting to drop something different?

508
00:52:32,125 --> 00:52:34,167
[SPEAKER_07]: of Vice President Bex, seconded by Councilor Carvalho.

509
00:52:34,568 --> 00:52:35,208
[SPEAKER_07]: All those in favor?

510
00:52:35,949 --> 00:52:36,670
[SPEAKER_07]: Opposed?

511
00:52:36,830 --> 00:52:38,352
[SPEAKER_07]: Motion passes and meeting adjourned.

